<p>Peru’s interim president José Jerí declared a 30-day state of emergency for metropolitan Lima and the neighbouring port of Callao on Tuesday, citing a surge in crime and weeks of anti-government protests over corruption and organised crime [reuters.com#1][scmp.com#1][aljazeera.com#2]. The decree, approved by the council of ministers and announced on state television, takes effect at midnight on Wednesday and authorises deployment of the armed forces while suspending certain constitutional rights, including freedom of assembly [guardian.com#1][aljazeera.com#2][elpais.com#1]. Officials said the move aims to combat rising killings, violent extortion and attacks on public places that have alarmed residents and intensified street demonstrations [thehindu.com#1][scmp.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/J-3hHkIqcF4ZbmWsWirz5NpNbluZih9OTwSTxYkvzJcsu4WbStdI64TdPDHnTqcC9wyeBVsWl0uwNBaLZUnVvqYInlO0yXtKkXYr0OqE0oqz7jMaprSBX3pOQmrmOruniPOCbponDhht86Ccnp2-20ezmawLIgDbDVMm1VhrGR5eoGV8SBDJXpSUAmBsRXoZcRJPbZuVJzOZTO3XuMUypMyCwTvFo4TR6hu2Ifs' alt='Protests against José Jerí in Arequipa, Peru, on October 15.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Presidential rhetoric: Jerí framed the measure as switching &quot;from defense to offense,&quot; using forceful language such as &quot;wars are won with actions, not words&quot; to justify the move [elpais.com#1][firstpost.com#1]</li><li>Types of crime: Authorities singled out a recent uptick in killings, violent extortion and attacks on public places as drivers of the emergency declaration [thehindu.com#1][scmp.com#1]</li><li>Political context: Weeks of anti-government protests over corruption and organised crime increased pressure on the interim government after the downfall of the previous president, helping prompt the decree [scmp.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1]</li></ul><blockquote>Wars are won with actions, not words - José Jerí</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Interim president José Jerí / Peruvian government: The government says the emergency is needed to restore security and &#x27;move from defense to offense&#x27; against rising crime. (<a href='https://english.elpais.com/international/2025-10-22/perus-interim-president-declares-state-of-emergency-in-lima-and-callao-wars-are-won-with-actions-not-words.html'>El País</a>)</li><li>Anti-government protesters and civil society: Protesters who have demonstrated for weeks against corruption and organised crime worry the decree will curtail civil liberties and restrict the right to protest. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/22/state-of-emergency-declared-in-perus-capital-lima-amid-protests'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/video/newsfeed/2025/10/22/video-peru-declares-30-day-state-of-emergency-in-lima-amid-rising-crime'>Video: Peru declares 30-day state of emergency in Lima amid rising crime</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/Peru-declares-30-day-state-of-emergency-in-Lima-to-tackle-rising-crime'>Peru declares 30-day state of emergency in Lima to tackle rising crime</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://english.elpais.com/international/2025-10-22/perus-interim-president-declares-state-of-emergency-in-lima-and-callao-wars-are-won-with-actions-not-words.html'>Peru’s interim president declares state of emergency in Lima and Callao: ‘Wars are won with actions, not words’</a> - elpais.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3329895/peru-declares-state-emergency-capital-combat-spiralling-crime'>Peru declares state of emergency in capital to combat spiralling crime</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/perus-president-jose-jeri-declares-state-of-emergency-in-lima-to-tackle-surging-violence/article70188914.ece'>Peru&#x27;s President Jose Jeri declares state of emergency in Lima to tackle surging violence</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/w